Barn: Nils-Håkan f. 43, Mona 46. — Stud:ex. i Kristianstad 21, handelsstud. i TyskL, bl. a. vid handelssk. i Hamburg, 21-23, jur. kand. i Lund 29. Tingstjg. i Bräkne doms. 29-32, bitr. jurist å Axel Jönssons Adv :byrå i Karlshamn 32-44, inneh. sed. 44. Äg. jordbr :fastigh. i Hälilaryds s :n, vil’la i Karlshamn samt fastigheter i Bräkne-Hoby. Sekr. i Blek. läns lånend 32-38 o. i flera bok, ordf. i A-B J. Th. Asschier o. Blek. Ömsesid. translated: Håkansson, Inge, lawyer, Karlshamn, born January 23, 1902 in Bräkne-Hoby, Blekinge, first child of district prosecutor C.G. and Kerstin FL G., married Eva Fröhling in 1942, with children Nils-Håkan born in 1943 and Mona born in 1946. Inge underwent his studies at Kristianstad in 1921 and in Trade at various institutions in Germany, including the commercial school in Hamburg from 1921-1923, and graduated in law from Lund University in 1929. He served as an assessor at the Bräkne court from 1929-1932 and as a legal assistant at Axel Jönsson's law firm in Karlshamn from 1932-1944 before becoming the owner in 1944. He owned agricultural properties in Hälilaryds parish, a villa in Karlshamn and properties in Bräkne-Hoby. He served as a secretary in Blekinge County's loan association from 1932-1938, and in several positions including Chairman of the Board at J. Th. Asschier AB and Blekinge Mutual Marine Insurance Association, as well as a representative for Karlshamn Stevedoring AB since 1944, all located in Karlshamn. He was also a secretary of the Karlshamn Motor Club since 1934, representative for the Royal Automobile Club and the Motorfederation since 1944 and became a member of the Swedish Bar Association in 1942. Hobbies include hunting, fishing, and motorsports.
